I asked the AI ChatGPT if it knew what a 4 track recorder was and then it told me all about it. I asked if it knew what a cassette tapeloop was and it told me what it was and how to make one. I then asked it to give me examples of what to record to each track on the tapeloop and this is what it gave me:
Track 1 - traffic ambience 
Track 2 - spoken word from a radio broadcast
Track 3 - experimental guitar
Track 4 - take the first 3 tracks and effect them with delay

And that is what you are hearing. Our days are numbered 🫠🫠
#guitarpedal #diy #fuzz #guitar #music #experimental #pedal #DIYmusic #guitareffects #guitarsound #chatgpt #tapeloop 
It even picked the hashtags 🫠🫠

Here’s 2 ways to use Transit. 
The first way is having the “loop” and “pendulum” settings turned on, it acts as an effects sequencer sorta lol I have mine in an odd loop division to get that evolving feel.
The second way is something i stumbled on. By setting the pitch to be motion controlled and setting the pitch range i can use the Transit knob as a tape speed control. And it’s pretty convincing!
There’s a lot more to this plugin then meets the eye!
